p: The methanol fraction (24.1 mg) was eluted with methanol and water (9 : 1, v/v) to yield a brown solid. Phytochemical screening of this fraction revealed the presence of tannins and amide bonds. This fraction tested negative for saponins, sterols, reducing sugars, flavonoids, and terpenoids. The NMR spectra (Supplementary Figures 5 and 6), HRESIMS (Supplementary Figure 7), and IR spectrum (Supplementary Figure 8) of the methanol fraction indicated the presence of aromatic and aliphatic groups attributable to aromatic compounds and fatty acids.
